data.content:
Here are the three EF Core 10 breaking changes affecting your code and how to fix each:

---

## 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` — now accepts a regular lambda

The API changed from `Expression<Func<...>>` to `Action<...>`. Your expression tree construction no longer compiles. Replace with a simple lambda:

```csharp
// .NET 10 — no expression trees needed
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

---

## 2. Complex type column names are now uniquified/use full path

Two changes hit you:
- **Shared property names** (e.g., `Street` on both `ShippingAddress` and `BillingAddress`) get a numeric suffix appended.
- **Nested complex types** now use the full path: `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` maps to `Payment_BillingAddress_City` (was `BillingAddress_City`).

Both generate a rename migration. To preserve existing column names, pin them explicitly:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b => {
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, sa => {
        sa.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("ShippingAddress_Street");
    });
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, ba => {
        ba.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_Street");
    });
});

// For nested complex types:
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>(b => {
    b.ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment, p => {
        p.ComplexProperty(pay => pay.BillingAddress, ba => {
            ba.Property(a => a.City).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");
        });
    });
});
```

---

## 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` — new `logCommandText` parameter

All methods like `CommandReaderExecuting` now require an additional `string logCommandText` parameter (redacted SQL for safe logging):

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection, DbCommand command,
        DbContext context, Guid commandId, Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)          // ← add this
    {
        // Use logCommandText for logging (constants may be redacted)
        // Use command.CommandText for actual SQL
    }
}
```

Add the same parameter to all other methods in the interface (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.).
